<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer4630546850582648056">Michael J. Sandel is an American political philosopher who lives in Brookline, Massachusetts. He is the Anne T. and Robert M. Bass Professor of Government at Harvard University, where he has taught since 1980. He is best known for the Harvard course &apos;Justice&apos;, which is available to view online, and for his critique of John Rawls&apos; <i>A Theory of Justice</i> in his first book, <i>Liberalism and the Limits of </i></span>
  <span id="freeText4630546850582648056" style="display:none">Michael J. Sandel is an American political philosopher who lives in Brookline, Massachusetts. He is the Anne T. and Robert M. Bass Professor of Government at Harvard University, where he has taught since 1980. He is best known for the Harvard course 'Justice', which is available to view online, and for his critique of John Rawls' <i>A Theory of Justice</i> in his first book, <i>Liberalism and the Limits of Justice</i> (1982). He was elected a Fellow of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences in 2002.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4630546850582648056" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

